<center><h2>Ucigame - Reference on Colors</h2></center>


<h4>
<a href="index.html">Home</a> |
<a href="getting-started.html">Getting Started</a> |
<a href="reference.html">Reference</a> |
<a href="java.html">Introduction to Java</a> |
<a href="gallery.html">Gallery</a>
</h4>

<p>
Colors in Ucigame are specified in one of two ways:
</p>
<ul>
<li>With three numbers, indicating the red, green, and blue components.
<li>With one number, indicating white, black, or a shade of gray.
</ul>

<p>
In both cases, the number or number range from 0 to 255.
Other values have no meaning.
</p>
<p>
Here are some examples with three numbers:
</p>
<table border>
<tr> <td> 255, 0, 0					<td width="100" bgcolor="#FF0000"> &nbsp;	<td> Pure, maximum red
<tr> <td> 0, 255, 0					<td width="100" bgcolor="#00FF00"> &nbsp;	<td> Pure, maximum green
<tr> <td> 0, 0, 255					<td width="100" bgcolor="#0000FF"> &nbsp;	<td> Pure, maximum blue
<tr> <td> 255, 255, 255&nbsp;&nbsp;	<td width="100" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> &nbsp;	<td> White: all colors at maximum
<tr> <td> 0, 0, 0					<td width="100" bgcolor="#000000"> &nbsp;	<td> Black: all colors at minimum
<tr> <td> 255, 64, 164				<td width="100" bgcolor="#FF4040"> &nbsp;	<td> Full red, some green and blue
<tr> <td> 255, 128, 128				<td width="100" bgcolor="#FF8080"> &nbsp;	<td> Full red, medium green and blue
<tr> <td> 255, 192, 192				<td width="100" bgcolor="#FFCCCC"> &nbsp;	<td> Full red, lots o' green and blue
<tr> <td> 128, 128, 128				<td width="100" bgcolor="#808080"> &nbsp;	<td> Equal amounts of three colors yields a shade of gray
<tr> <td> 255, 255, 0				<td width="100" bgcolor="#FFFF00"> &nbsp;	<td> Yellow is red plus green
<tr> <td> 255, 0, 255				<td width="100" bgcolor="#FF00FF"> &nbsp;	<td> Purple is red plus blue
<tr> <td> 0, 255, 255				<td width="100" bgcolor="#00FFFF"> &nbsp;	<td> Teal is green plus blue
<tr> <td> 128, 0, 0					<td width="100" bgcolor="#800000"> &nbsp;	<td> Dark red
<tr> <td> 128, 128, 0				<td width="100" bgcolor="#808000"> &nbsp;	<td> Dark yellow
</table>

<p>
Here are some examples with one number:
</p>

<table border>
<tr> <td> 255					<td width="100" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> &nbsp;	<td> Pure, maximum white
<tr> <td> 200					<td width="100" bgcolor="#C8C8C8"> &nbsp;	<td> Light gray
<tr> <td> 150					<td width="100" bgcolor="#969696"> &nbsp;	<td> Gray
<tr> <td> 128					<td width="100" bgcolor="#808080"> &nbsp;	<td> Medium gray
<tr> <td> 100					<td width="100" bgcolor="#646464"> &nbsp;	<td> Darker gray
<tr> <td> 50					<td width="100" bgcolor="#323232"> &nbsp;	<td> Dark gray
<tr> <td> 0						<td width="100" bgcolor="#000000"> &nbsp;	<td> Black
</table>


